<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2012-06-01</DATELINE><TITLE>Human rhinovirus infections in symptomatic and asymptomatic subjects</TITLE><BODY>The role of rhinovirus asymptomatic infections in the transmission among close contacts subjects is unknown. We tested health care workers, a pair of one child and a family member and immunocompromised patients (n =191). HRV were detected on 22.9% symptomatic and 3.6% asymptomatic cases suggesting lower transmission among contacts.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>